<h2>What does "hiccup" mean?</h2>
<p>Sometimes a site goes down and Joule, instead of realising it should skip a
day, registers that a user has no friends instead. This has the effect of all
users appearing to unfriend and then immediately refriend a user. So, if more than
thirty people add or delete you on the same day, Joule will display "hiccup"
on that day. If it was wrong to do so, you can include the <code>nohiccup=1</code>
parameter to turn this off. Eventually I will go through and purge these from
the database, but there's a lot of more urgent things to do right now.</p>

